Dr Shirley Coetzee


To run the netrad database 
--------------------------

1) Install MySQL on Linux. (I used Linux 14.04, Trusty Tahr)

2) Enter the following commands in MySQL:
mysql -uroot -pHello123;
CREATE DATABASE netrad;
SHOW DATABASES;
USE netrad;

3) To create the tables, copy the contents of make_tables.txt into MySQL. To delete the tables, copy the contents of drop_tables.txt into MySQL.

4) Enter the following command in MySQL to check the tables:
SHOW TABLES;

5) To view the structure of a table (e.g. table config) type:
DESCRIBE config;

6) To load data from a netrad e*.m file (e.g. e14_05_08_1316_07_P1_1_200_S0_1_2047_node3.m) to the database in MySQL enter the following and enter your linux password (NOT your MySQL password 'Hello123'):
sudo ./net









